  "prompt": "Do VoLTE calls work with data switched off?",
  "response": "VoLTE (Voice over LTE) calls typically require a data connection because they use the LTE network to transmit voice calls instead of traditional circuit-switched voice channels. However, if you have VoLTE enabled and you're in an area where VoLTE is supported by your carrier, you can make and receive calls without turning on mobile data as long as your phone's settings allow for it and you have an active LTE connection for voice.\n\nThat said, if \"data\" refers to mobile data being completely turned off and it's not just mobile data toggled off for background usage, then VoLTE calls may not function because they rely on the LTE network for voice.\n\nIn summary:\n- VoLTE calls require a functional LTE connection.\n- If \"data switched off\" means that mobile data is completely off, VoLTE calls won't work.\n- If you have LTE enabled but are limiting mobile data usage, you may still be able to make VoLTE calls.\n\nAlways check with your carrier for specific details related to your plan and device capabilities.",
